      <div type="description" n="monument">
        <head>Description of Monument</head>
        <p>Twenty-two <rs type="material" key="marmor">white marble</rs> fragments, some joining, from the outer rim of a large <rs type="objectType" reg="circular crowning feature">circular feature</rs> (outer diam. <measure dim="diameter" type="length">3</measure> m, inner <measure dim="diameter" type="length">2.55</measure>). The blocks were designed to be seen from below, and have elaborately ornamented trapezoidal panels on the underside (each <measure precision="circa" type="length" dim="none">0.98</measure> long); the panels each have a different pattern, which enables the grouping together of several fragments which do not join. The blocks are slightly convex, and the outer edge slopes outwards from bottom to top (H. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.16</measure>); on it are a series of bosses with an ornamental cross (<measure precision="circa" type="length" dim="none">0.40</measure> apart).</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="text">
        <head>Description of Text</head>
        <p>The text runs in one line between the bosses, with a continuous line incised above and below it.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="letters">
        <head>Description of Letters</head>
        <p>av. <measure type="length" unit="metre" dim="height">0.09</measure>; deep triangular trenches; elongated and ornate. Colon for stop in a after <foreign lang="grc">φύσιν</foreign>, and in b: semi-colon in a after <foreign lang="grc">ΡΙΣ</foreign>; horizontal line over abbreviation in k.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="description" n="date">
        <head>Date</head>
        <p><date notAfter="1000" exact="none" notBefore="0901">Tenth century A.D.</date> (<rs type="criteria">architecture</rs>, <rs type="criteria">terminology</rs>)</p>
      </div>

